			<div><strong>Color of Spell Name Text in the Spell book</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
			<div class="smallfont">1 Attachment(s)</div>
		
		
		<div>I redrew on Quartz (which is a great UI) so that I could have a Trigun theme.  Only problem left is that Vash's cloak being partially black hides some of the spell text.  My question is how do I change the font of certain spell slots in the spell book.  I know enough about XML so that i can fiddle with it without messing things up too much, but need assistance with every step.  Here's a screenshot of the UI.</div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
<br /><table class="tborder" cellpadding="6" cellspacing="1" border="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td class="page">
	
		<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
		<tr valign="bottom">
			<td style="font-size:14pt">Pure</td>
			<td class="smallfont" align="right">08-18-2002 11:47 PM</td>
		</tr>
		</table>
		
		<hr />
		
		
			<div><strong>SpellBook Text Color</strong><br />&nbsp;</div>
		
		
		
		<div>To change the font color look below:<br />
<div style="margin:20px; margin-top:5px;">
	<div class="smallfont" style="margin-bottom:2px">Quote:</div>
	<table cellpadding="6" cellspacing="0" border="0">
	<tr>
		<td class="alt2" style="border:1px">
			
				
&lt;StaticText item =&quot;SBW_SpellName0&quot;&gt;<br />
		&lt;ScreenID&gt;SBW_SpellName0&lt;/ScreenID&gt;<br />
		&lt;Font&gt;2&lt;/Font&gt;<br />
		&lt;TextColor&gt;<br />
				&lt;R&gt;0&lt;/R&gt;<br />
				&lt;G&gt;0&lt;/G&gt;<br />
				&lt;B&gt;240&lt;/B&gt;<br />
		&lt;/TextColor&gt;<br />
		&lt;RelativePosition&gt;true&lt;/RelativePosition&gt;<br />
		&lt;Location&gt;<br />
			&lt;X&gt;100&lt;/X&gt;<br />
			&lt;Y&gt;50&lt;/Y&gt;<br />
		&lt;/Location&gt;<br />
		&lt;Size&gt;<br />
			&lt;CX&gt;100&lt;/CX&gt;<br />
			&lt;CY&gt;16&lt;/CY&gt;<br />
		&lt;/Size&gt;<br />
		&lt;Text&gt;Complete Healing&lt;/Text&gt;<br />
		&lt;NoWrap&gt;false&lt;/NoWrap&gt;<br />
		&lt;AlignCenter&gt;true&lt;/AlignCenter&gt;<br />
		&lt;AlignRight&gt;false&lt;/AlignRight&gt;<br />
	&lt;/StaticText&gt;<br />
			
		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>
</div><br />
<br />
Every spell from 0 -15 you need to add this:<br />
&lt;TextColor&gt;<br />
				&lt;R&gt;0&lt;/R&gt;<br />
				&lt;G&gt;0&lt;/G&gt;<br />
				&lt;B&gt;240&lt;/B&gt;<br />
		&lt;/TextColor&gt;<br />
<br />
You can change the colors to your desire:<br />
<a href="http://html-color-codes.com/rgb.html" target="_blank">RGB Color Codes</a></div>
	</td>
</tr>
</table>
